[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Exploring module creation**\n\nI’m thinking about creating an explicit named module instead of doing it automatically. I wonder if I can create a dynamic module-info without using stubs. It seems like I could make a jar with the module-info and possibly incorporate ByteBuddyAgent classes. However, I need to be cautious; using source stub/shadow classes in the real package isn't allowed. Perhaps I could utilize an upstream jar and then add the module-info?\n\n**Analyzing runtime issues**\n\nI’m thinking that runtime class loading might be unsupported. It seems better in native—maybe `ModuleLayer.define` could throw an UnsupportedFeatureError before the compiler? But first, we need to create a JAR. I wonder if we could avoid compiling at runtime by precompiling `module-info` as a test resource? But creating it under `src/test/java` might not work well.\n\nAlternatively, I could use `ModuleDescriptor.newModule(...).exports(...).requires(...).build()`, but the `ModuleInfoWriter` is internal, not public. Generating `module-info.class` bytes manually might be an option.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_08d5b14ff114f47a016a402d588ea88195907c2dd489d83632\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqQC12PmOuDLGEcZEpizCjquPsjsh-hlaLt9y5YmPYz-tEZRx2DIDl8xiAeeiwjsWml-d177Ta34oH2m461b0Ywqo-AxKWIDCbOF5GivuVikdZ6W3TVejZcnNf0cJNL2vuGVdIWp6Tz6h_F4K7tJTOke5YhsyG-qoWhoGgfcxoZloiUkaXhh6nSna0SPyPWQXOi8YuIN8mwptJl36_SAMiKiVHNPGTZ8NfoxO8MxMop5Xc74ozZGB1UhomZzc9Tk48YlsIwPYGYI8IolAi-znkd4G8jfaSaRL7jc9L9lPo22MgSsOSL6lD4dVJkfWuIAont6z3SAeW7-HWPv02pzx17KW4smkgQNl3A2GlIMZUDppNub5tHcBf2237DY9XiUy-r87Ws-BX9_AtxfdCSjxti49S4leyp6qVwiZOLxjGo4Z2745KycQiYvB-gFxJtFreHYE6in6b8MzBmD-9smupgA2KsjL2odtyLt5EJcZotX7cg323T7G7iUpQBGFNnezKwoqFBGziO-hThBCJ86_yqJv2ae8nsYXSkQNGDZ38STp2O0Kb-1sxW8_0eItSi9dpCxF7Ei0jF_nIjJtsM4HhzOb0HvMHq9QWNyfnAjhzV-XzZ3l5RtX6--jxlc7ygY1MtisVCFHYRk